resources.string:
Source and Demo code at https://github.com/danielemaddaluno/Android-Update-Checker

 If the Update Check is requested by a user action you can call the following code line (you can test this function by clicking the button above):
 new UpdateRunnable(this, new Handler()).force(true).start();

 Otherwise if you want to use the Update Checker automatically, you can call from the onCreate() of your activity the following code line, which will test for updates automatically once a day:
 new UpdateRunnable(this, new Handler()).start();

